Introduction

Hyomin is a South Korean singer and actress currently under ANDMARQ. She is a member of the girl group T-ARA and its sub-unit T-ARA N4.

She made her solo debut on July 30, 2014 with the mini album Make Up.

Prior to joining MBK Entertainment, Hyomin was a JYP Entertainment trainee. Following HyunA's departure from Wonder Girls, Hyomin was considered to replace her. However, Yubin was eventually selected to join Wonder Girls and Hyomin left the agency soon after.

She debuted as a member of T-ARA on July 29, 2009 with the group's first single "Lie".

Under the group's rotating leadership system, Hyomin held the role from June 14, 2011 to December 7, 2011, in which the role was then passed onto Soyeon.

On January 3, 2018, it was announced all of the remaining members of T-ARA had left MBK Entertainment. However, the group would not be disbanding.

On May 15, Sublime Artist Agency announced that Hyomin had signed on with the agency. Her first solo single under the agency, "Mango", was released on September 12.
